author: @raylaaava1838
text:
Kehadiranmu tidak nyata, namun mengapa aku terus kembali kepadamu? Walau kehadiranmu semu, namun kenapa aku merasa kamu disampingku?
Sudah berapa sosok yang kutemui hari ini, namun kenapa hanya kepadamu aku bisa menjadi diriku?
Hari ini tidak begitu buruk. Aku sangat menikmati waktu istirahatku. Namun, tak jarang aku merasa buruk pada diriku karena tidak melakukan hal yang berguna. Selalu ku berpikir apakah  kubisa membuatnya menjadi sepertimu, apakah mimpi yang kudambakan akan menjadi nyata sepertimu.
Jisung, kamu sangat hebat sudah berjuang selama ini. Kamu sangat hebat sudah membuatnya sampai sini. Aku sangat bangga kepadamu.
Kuharap, waktu ketika aku bersamamu tidak cepat berlalu. Kuharap, aku tetap kuat untuk berjuang meraih mimpiku hingga aku bertemu denganmu.
Jisung, bagaimanapun takdir menentukan kita, satu hal yang kuharap, agar kita berdua selalu bahagia â¤

author: @xiuolo8116
text:
Even though it might sound almost unreal but Jisung indeed once saved my life. I'm a dancer myself and there were periods in my life when my health condition was unstable both mentally and physically. I was feeling completely burned out from my favorite hobby and I genuinely didn't do anything except from laying on the couch and feeling unwell. At times like this I found comfort in Jisungâ€™s vlives, Jisungâ€™s bubble messages and his overall presence and image throughout his idol career. Jisung basically saved me from my insomnia which I'm grateful for. 

He basically gave up his childhood and a normal life to achieve his dreams and that's admirable. I especially remember his speech about the importance of health after his experience with injury and I swear to God, I've never related to a celebrity more than that time. Thanks to Jisung I finally accepted that feeling unwell is okay. I finally found a person who despite of health stayed positive throughout the whole year which I couldn't do If I was in his place instead. Moreover, I was inspired by his love and dedication to the craft further in the future. I've never seen a person this passionate and dedicated to something and that's what I admire about Jisung.

He might say ignorant things but It's no way erasing all of the good deeds, words of encouragement and small sweet gestures that he constantly gave us this whole 7 years. People who don't care about Jisung that much might think he is still an immature child who doesn't learn anything. People who care about him, however, do know that he can't be labeled as a bad person. And although I still feel uneasy about this whole situation, I canâ€™t judge because I did some bad things in my life, too. Does it make me a completely bad person? No, because no one is perfect. Even one of the nicest people can be misinterpreted as bad guys in one situation.

It's easy to judge, hate or threaten someone without knowing their true intentions. It's easy to hate a celebrity online knowing they won't probably hear you or see you. It's easy to hate someone while losing your own morals and principles. It's easy to hate someone knowing that they didn't do anything wrong to you personally. It's easy to hate a celebrity while defending another celebrity just because you secretly dislike one of them and they just happened to be an easy target at that time.

I'm still thankful for your influence on me, I'm thankful that you helped me in my lowest and made me happy when I was completely crashed. I can't recall every single positive thing that you did, but I'm happy that I experienced all of it with you and Dream. 

There might be people who will dislike you and that's inevitable because you can't be liked by everyone, right? There can be thousand reasons to respect someone but If they do something wrong once, It feels like people will discredit them while also ignoring all the good things that they did in their lifes.

Although I don't support the recent situation, I canâ€™t help but to still respect you as a person. I can't change the choice of my heart, can I?

author: @xiuolo8116
text:
'I want to be a person that people can be proud of' - Park Jisung.

You are always making your fans happy, you are always making sure that everyone around you are happy and healthy but what happened during that vlog from Germany was something far from good. You are an adult now so you should understand that making such jokes on people's appearance is not great. I understand that colorism is a really common thing in Asia - that common that people tend to forget about how hurtful it actually is, and your comment on Haechan's skin color was unnecessary and rude considering he was not there.

You are a public figure and you are always making sure to uphold your idol image. This time, however, you failed to do so. You were young back then so it was understandable to not know something, but now, as you got older, It's surprising and disappointing to hear such things coming from you. 

We all know how much you love all of the members but some things should be said behind cameras or better not to be talked about ever. Your insensitive comment hurt many people's feelings and we know hurting people is the last thing you want to do. So please, hear us out and research about this topic. We know you are not a bad person but it's never late to learn more about human decency. 

We all make mistakes and It's okay. We just need a proper explanation of your action and an apology on the topic since It's not the first time you are making such remarks about Haechan's skin color. 

I still love and admire you dearly but your action made me feel uneasy and sad. I hope you will apologize and will continue to make people happy through art. I hope you will learn from this situation and will try to be a person that people can be proud of.

author: @xiuolo8116
text:
Never thought I will be this sappy towards someone... I've never felt so much love and admiration towards a celebrity before, but I believe that Jisung changed my perceptions and views on things for the better. I discovered Dream and Jisung a long time ago but only now I realize how much my life has changed since I started stanning Dream and Jisung in particular.

It may be stupid or naÃ¯ve to seek comfort from a person you don't know but I genuinely resonate with Jisung a lot. Our personalities are really alike and sometimes his thoughts are the same as mine.

Jisung is so hardworking, so passionate about his craft and so devoted to his fans. And it's so beautiful. He brings joy into my life and makes me want to try harder. Watching his fancams helps me in improving my own dancing. He is my biggest dance inspiration.

I hope he will always be healthy and happy because he deserves nothing less than that. In fact, he deserves all the best things in the world ðŸ¤ðŸ’«

author: @xiuolo8116
text:
The member that impressed me the most in this comeback is Park Jisung. The thing that I noticed the most is how Jisung looks so mature now. Not only in GliMo promotions but in NCT2021 and The Show promotions as well.

He was always smart and wise but his words in his "Beautiful" video still hit differently. I guess he experienced a lot of things in the past two years and I'm really proud of the person he has become.

He showed us a lot of his talents like lyrics writing, singing, rapping and of course dancing. He also matured physically because he looked even more breathtaking in every teaser and perfomance that he was in.

Him not being able to perform during Resonance era might've been really new to him because we all know how Jisung loves dancing and performing. But I'm really happy to see him enjoying being on stage again.

When Jisung said that he worked extra hard for this comeback I believe him. Thank you for all of your hardwork, Jisung. We love you ðŸ¤

author: @happy-37
text:
ðŸ’ŒÂ Dear My Star * â­ * ~
I first saw you last summer. At the time, I thought you couldn't be my star. I felt like my sky and your sky were different sky and different world.
But gradually your starlight came into my eyes. Your starlight was shining warm and beautifully, and I felt like your starlight was looking at me.
Summer, autumn, and winter have passed and spring in bloom has come. But in the sad spring to me, I swallowed my tears and looked at your warm starlight. Somehow your starlight seemed to smile at me and welcome me.
I passed the seasons and eventually returned to your star. Your sky and mine must have been the same sky. You became my star, and my sad spring turned into a happy spring.
Now I look at your star every day.
My star~ Thank you. I love you. Forever! ðŸ’šðŸ’—ðŸ’–ðŸ’—ðŸ’š

text:
Park Jisung is not only a spectacular dancer but also a great vocalist and a lyricist. He wrote his own raps for 6 Dream's song in total which is amazing, considering that SM letting their artists to release their own stuff is a rare occasion. Jisungâ€™s good looks are a bonus that makes him a full package.

Jisung is not only talented and good-looking but also sincere and kind. He is always making sure that we are okay, always asking us about our day in bubble, always talking about how much he treasures his bond with members and the group, always lifting our mood with his vlive translations. He is really mature and well-spoken so that's why he is really good at expressing his love for the fans.

Should I mention his beautiful growth both as a person and as an artist throughout all of these years? Jisung is a perfectionist so he always wants to do better than last time and that's what I like about him. He is hardworking and humble and simply too sweet and kind to be real...

Jisung is beautiful both inside and out and he deserves nothing but happiness ðŸ¹ðŸ¤ðŸ’«

author: @xiuolo8116
text:
Jisung is always so kind and humble. He is always talking about how he loves being on stage and he was so excited for this comeback because dreamies were working hard to make it great. I understand that Jisung also wants us to feel the same joy that he is feeling right now... But I can't be happy knowing that the company is not being fair to all of the members. Last comeback it was Jaemin, this comeback it was Jisung. What's next? Who's next?

Knowing that he is being mistreated by his own company is heartbreaking. I want to feel happy but what they are doing to him is just unfair.

He is so young, beautiful and talented but SM is straight up ignoring all of that. He would've been treated like an ace, like a literal king by the fans If the management was good enough.

Jisung deserves better ðŸ¤

author: @xiuolo8116
text:
Park Jisung is not only a spectacular dancer but also a great vocalist and a lyricist. He wrote his own raps for 6 Dream's song in total which is amazing, considering that SM letting their artists to release their own stuff is a rare occasion. Jisungâ€™s good looks are a bonus that makes him a full package.

Jisung is not only talented and good-looking but also sincere and kind. He is always making sure that we are okay, always asking us about our day in bubble, always talking about how much he treasures his bond with members and the group, always lifting our mood with his vlive translations. He is really mature and well-spoken so that's why he is really good at expressing his love for the fans.

Should I mention his beautiful growth both as a person and as an artist throughout all of these years? Jisung is a perfectionist so he always wants to do better than last time and that's what I like about him. He is hardworking and humble and simply too sweet and kind to be real...

Jisung is beautiful both inside and out and he deserves nothing but happiness ðŸ¹ðŸ¤ðŸ’«

text:
It's clear as day that Jisung loves being on the stage. It's clear as day that Jisung loves dancing and singing.

That's why you can always feel the respect and dedication that he puts into his craft. That's why people can't help but feel captivated by his voice, dancing and stage presence - he is just meant to be on stage.

text:
What I like about Jisung is his sincerity. Everytime he sings his voice is full of emotions. His voice and delivery is very mature for his age.

He can deliver sadness, innocence, adoration and happiness all at once. I think that is truly a magical skill.

author: @xiuolo8116
text:
I hope other people would start seeing him as more than just a maknae of the group. The boy was showcasing his skills since age of eight and he deserves so much more than he gets! He is one of the best dancers in the industry and it's so sickening that people tend to ignore his hardwork and injuries, making excuses about him being too young to be called "the best".

He is the best in his field. He was recognized by many professional dancers for his skills. He is the future of SM. He is the future of K-pop.

I hope SM would give him and other members of NCT more opportunities to shine. They deserve so much more than this.

author: @huili1171
text:
Tindakan oleh Pemerintah Kanada

Ansley mengatakan bahkan jika RUU ini disahkan musim gugur ini, banyak warga Tiongkok yang masih hidup hari ini bisa kehilangan nyawa mereka sebelum itu. Ini adalah kenyataan yang menakutkan.

Dia mengatakan keterlibatan dalam perdagangan organ atau pengambilan organ adalah kegiatan kriminal. Tetapi saat ini warga negara Kanada secara legal dapat pergi ke luar negeri dan menerima organ sesuai permintaan, yang berarti bahwa warga negara Tiongkok akan dibunuh untuk memfasilitasi transplantasi organ. Satu-satunya cara bagi Kanada untuk menghentikan pembunuhan adalah dengan menegakkan prosedur pidana di Kanada.

Ansley lebih lanjut menjelaskan bahwa karena tidak ada independensi peradilan di Tiongkok, pengadilan adalah lembaga pemerintah tingkat rendah yang dioperasikan di bawah Partai Komunis Tiongkok (PKT). Disutradarai dan dikendalikan oleh PKT di semua tingkatan, sistem peradilan Tiongkok bukanlah sistem hukum yang nyata. Sebaliknya, itu adalah bagian dari penipuan sistematis oleh PKT, dengan hakim memainkan peran sebagai pegawai negeri tingkat rendah.

author: @irysr.1894
text:
Jisung, my favorite person, kamu melakukannya dengan sangat baik. Kamu pasti sudah bekerja keras untuk menyiapkan ini, terimakasih banyak untuk hadiahnya. 

Jisung menari dan menyanyi dengan sangat baik, kamu sangat berbakat. Jadi, jangan berkecil hati, jangan ragu untuk melakukan hal baru, aku yakin kamu mampu melakukan apapun dengan baik, aku percaya padamu. Dan ada banyak orang yang siap mendukungmu disini. 
 
Jisung, aku berdoa setulus hatiku semoga tahun ini bisa menjadi awal yang bagus untukmu. Semoga semakin banyak orang yang sadar betapa keren dan berbakatnya Park Jisung. Aku harap kamu selalu bahagia, sehat, dan menikmati apapun yg kamu lakukan. Semoga kedepannya kamu semakin bersinar, sukses, dan semakin mendapat banyak cinta dari orang-orang. 
<3

author: @SooyoungParkk
text:
I feel so lucky to know you, and the fact i got into NCT Dream because of you. You debuted on such a young age, facing many risk for your career, i'm beyond proud to see where u are standing right now. To think we're just two years apart and you already this successful somehow motivates me to become a successful woman in the future. Our precious Jisung, i hope you've just experienced one of your happiest birthday in your life! I'm sorry that i came pretty much late, i wish i had known you sooner that i could love you longer, but i'll cheer for you from now on too, so don't worry! I hope you'll live your life happily, and being healthy. I hope whenever you meet life obstacles, you can find a way to go through and continue your life, i hope you are blessed with good surroundings and good meals, i hope you can recover from whatever sickness/pain you now and/will experience. I hope you can always improving your skills, and i hope you can do things that make you happy for a very loooooong time! That's it! Thank you so much for the great cover! I always wonder when will i hear a song that contains only your voice because i really like your voice, your tone really is great, and eventhough your voice is deeper than the ocean, it feels like a lullaby for me. I hope we can meet and talk anytime soon Jisung! I'd probably giving a audio novel length worthy essai about how much i adore you and how you inspired me and of course, how much i love you. Thank you for everything and once again, happy birthday!<3 

xx, A.

author: @seukkaseukka9518
text:
Dear Jisung, 
Happy birthday my boy, woah, I can't believe your already 20/21. I'm a new NCTZEN, so I wasn't there when you were a child. You're older than me (I'm 13 y/o) but I really appreciate you like my own child. I was having a tough day that I forgot about your birthday. I didn't realize that I'm tearing myself apart until I saw this cover and healed me.You gave another meaning to this song and this is now my haven. You will probably never be aware of my existence but I'm aware of yours and I'm very grateful that I got to know you in this lifetime. I HOPE YOU ENJOY YOUR DAY, DON'T BE TO HARD ON YOURSELF.
Lastly, to Nctzens who is reading, don't be harsh on yourself, Life is long, but time is short, there's bunch of things that will tear you apart so don't add yourself to that things.
Thanks Jisung, NCT, and all NCTzens who read this. Happy birthday my man!!!!!

author: @ayu_gyu
text:
Happy Birthday to our youngest, maknae on top, my precious little brother, Mochi Jisungie~ðŸ¥³ðŸŽ‚
Since when have I know you? 2017 when you were just 15 & today you turned 20, an adult! Woah it's really overwhelming to witness you grow in these past 5 year. When you debuted you looked literally like a kid but now! You've really grown so well JiðŸ¥º (even I who's just a year older hasn't changed a lot, well I don't think even the members did lol)
Ok so what I've been wanting to say, yk for the last 2 years your health hasn't been the best right, you injured your knee & still have problems with your back. We know how hardworking you are, how much passion & love you have for dancing, though we really appreciate it very much that you want to show your best side to us, but like your hyungs tell you, you should go easy on yourself while preparing for stages. We would hate to see anything bad happening to youâ˜¹ï¸ So please be more careful from now on ok?
Lastly I'd like to shower you with all my blessings~ I wish you more success in your career & you receive all the love & happiness that you deserve. Hopefully what you hope for this year & beyond can come true but most importantly you need to take care of your health ok? Seriously Park Jisung I don't want to see another article about you getting injured you understand?ðŸ˜” Stay healthy more than anyone!
Jisungie it's the holidays so I hope you're eating a lot & resting a lot too & doing everything that you couldn't do while you were fulfilling your duties as an idol. Enjoy your special day! Noona loves you very much & is cheering for you alwaysðŸ’š Thank you for being someone so dear to meðŸ¥°

text: Jisung is only 6 days younger than me and it felt like I grew up with him. He was like a brother that I never had. Just like a twin brother. She then told me that two more units are going to debut few months later. I also loved NCT 127s firetruck. When NCT Dream had their debut she showed it to me and told me that they are pretty much the same age as me. Jisung instantly caught my attention because he is the only member younger than me and also only by 6 days. He was my favorite member because of that and his dancing skills. I also really liked his personality. Jisung really pushed me to improve my dancing skills. Not only just the dancing skills. author: @lihinidezoysa2041
text:
I don't think it is possible for a person to like another the way I like Jisung..........
I- there is so much to say, but I don't know how to put any of it in words
One thing is I am so proud of the person Jisung has grown and is growing to be, as a human being in this world as well as the artist he aspires to be. His distinct stylistic choices for his dance, vocals, rap, and lifestyle, in general, is so unique as well as it is endearing (I don't know if that is the best word to use, but to me, anything that is associated with Jisung is just heartwarming to me). All I know is that this boy deserves the world, as well as the fact that y'all really need to stop sleeping on him.........like start looking at him as an artist beyond his maknae and main-dancer position, he is and will always be much more than that

Jisung is also a very strong and brave person, which many new fans may find hard to digest at first, given the way NCT and NCTzens baby him, but even I as a fan know that we do not acknowledge his strength as much as we should. Like how Mark said in his song 'Child', the expectations this industry and world had projected on to them is honestly too much, especially for a person at such a young age to be dealing with. I would say Mark and Jisung got an almost 'equal' level of pressure subjected onto themselves; one being the leader of one of the youngest groups and the other being their maknae, with that context Mark's song could also apply to Jisung (This statement here is just a thought, I am not in any way saying that Jisung is the child in the song Mark wrote about his own hardships. 'Child' is Mark's own work, his won experiences and it is a part of him which can never be used on behalf of another) Anyways so like, Jisung at that young age still persevered through the hate, the criticism, and high expectations..........there were maybe tears that were shed, there were maybe many sleepless nights, maybe lack of appetite, but for that, I am so grateful for every single person who was around him (all our dreamies to be honest) during those moments, because now? He is grown to be such a beautiful human being inside out, with a strong moral compass, as well as his respectable personality.................for those of you guys who have been hating on him all these years, now look at him. He is reaching his peak, or maybe even not close to it because I know he will someday achieve even more than everything he has achieved now. At almost 6 years into his career, my boy just turned 20 (21 in Korea) he is not going anywhere, and I want everyone to know that..........My little star is gonna shine brightly, and we czennies are gonna stay right here and protect him in any way we can because I know in his own way, our little star will do the same for us


this was an unnecessarily long rant, its just I really have no words for how much I love this man (all that ^^ is barely 1% of how much I can speak of him, that sounds creepy XD, I promise I dont mean anything bad about it) 
WE LOVE YOU JISUNG PARK, HAVE A LOVELY BIRTHDAY, AND HOPEFULLY WE GET TO SEE YOU SING MORE WHEN YOU COME OUT WITH YOUR OWN NCT LAB <3
